==English==
===Etymology===
Coined in the early twentieth century from {{Gr.}} [[δέκα]] (ten) + [[καί]] (and) + [[τρεῖς]] (three) + [[-phobia]]

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˌtrɪskaɪdɛkəˈfəʊbiə/}}, {{AHD|/trĭs'kī-dĕk'ə-fō'bē-ə/}}, {{SAMPA|['trIs kaI dEk ə 'foU biə]}}
*{{audio|en-us-triskaidekaphobia.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-əʊbiə|-əʊbiə]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# [[fear|Fear]], [[hate]], or [[dislike]] of the number [[thirteen]] ([[13]])
# {{italbrac|by extension}}: Fear of [[Friday]] the [[13th]].

